PropertyEntry.Name: target.network-default-interface-type
PropertyEntry.Description: Default network interface type. Typical options: null, ETHERNET, WIFI, CELLULAR, MESH

PropertyEntry.Name: target.flash_dual_bank
PropertyEntry.Description: Default board configuration is Single Bank Flash. If you enable Dual Bank with ST Link Utility, set value to 1

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.force-non-copyable-error
PropertyEntry.Description: Force compile time error when a NonCopyable object is copied

PropertyEntry.Name: target.lpticker_lptim
PropertyEntry.Description: This target supports LPTIM. Set value 1 to use LPTIM for LPTICKER, or 0 to use RTC wakeup timer

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.poll-use-lowpower-timer
PropertyEntry.Description: Enable use of low power timer class for poll(). May cause missing events.

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.stdio-flush-at-exit
PropertyEntry.Description: Enable or disable the flush of standard I/O's at exit.

PropertyEntry.Name: target.clock_source
PropertyEntry.Description: Mask value : USE_PLL_HSE_EXTC | USE_PLL_HSE_XTAL (need HW patch) | USE_PLL_HSI

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.stdio-buffered-serial
PropertyEntry.Description: Use UARTSerial driver to obtain buffered serial I/O on stdin/stdout/stderr. If false, unbuffered serial_getc and serial_putc are used directly.

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.default-serial-baud-rate
PropertyEntry.Description: Default baud rate for a Serial or RawSerial instance (if not specified in the constructor)

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.error-all-threads-info
PropertyEntry.Description: Reports all the threads in the system as part of error report.

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.max-error-filename-len
PropertyEntry.Description: Sets the maximum length of buffer used for capturing the filename in error context. This needs error-filename-capture-enabled feature.

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.error-hist-size
PropertyEntry.Description: Set the number of most recent errors the system keeps in its history, needs error-hist-enabled set to true for this to work.

PropertyEntry.Name: target.d11_configuration
PropertyEntry.Description: Value: PA_7 for the default board configuration, PB_5 in case of solder bridge update (SB121 off/ SB122 on)

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.stdio-convert-tty-newlines
PropertyEntry.Description: Enable conversion to standard newlines on any tty FILE stream

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.error-filename-capture-enabled
PropertyEntry.Description: Enables capture of filename and line number as part of error context capture, this works only for debug and develop builds. On release builds, filename capture is always disabled

PropertyEntry.Name: platform.stdio-convert-newlines
PropertyEntry.Description: Enable conversion to standard newlines on stdin/stdout/stderr

PropertyEntry.Name: target.lse_available
PropertyEntry.Description: Define if a Low Speed External xtal (LSE) is available on the board (0 = No, 1 = Yes). If Yes, the LSE will be used to clock the RTC, LPUART, ... otherwise the Low Speed Internal clock (LSI) will be used

Suggestion.UserFriendlyName: Newlib-nano with floating point support in printf()
Newlib-nano with floating point support in printf() and scanf()
